	<h1>Timber Transport License</h1>
	<form>

		<div class="">
		<p>All forest products removed from State forests must be accompanied by correct transportation documents issued by the Forest Department of within Sri Lanka. All naturalresources
        that have an impact on people's prosperity are controlled and utilized by the StateGovernment. Forests are one of these resources. Because forest products are classified asState assets, the Government regulates the administration and distribution of these products.</p>

		<h2>Requirements</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>Timer had to be obtained form a land owned by the applicant or timber has to be purchased legally.</li>
            <li>When those species of timber belong to the group of prohibited species under the flora and fauna protection ordinance,you should have a permit obtained from the director 
            general department of wild life conservation.</li>
		</ol>

		<h2>Required documents</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>Documents related to purchasing of timber.</li>
            <li>When timber has been taken from private land, should produce the documents related to private ownership of the land(Ex: Deeds).</li>
		</ol>

		<h4>Situations that deviate from above requirements and special information.</h4>
		<p>Timber that can be transported within each district without a permit has been published in Gazette No. 1548/29 of 09.05.2008 and No.1762/1 of 11 June 2012.</p>

